'''Angelo Nicolas Stiller''' ({{IPA|de|ˈandʒelo ˈʃtɪlɐ|-|}}; born 4 April 2001) is a German professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfB Stuttgart]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].

==Early life==
Born in [[Munich]], Germany, Stiller has a [[cleft lip]], which affects the shape of his nose.<ref name="bbcsportnov25">{{cite news |title=Player fined for mocking appearance of opponent born with cleft pallet |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cpd6x0n5j6xo |website=BBC News |access-date=November 29, 2025 |date=November 29, 2025 |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
=== Bayern Munich ===
Stiller made his professional debut for [[FC Bayern Munich II|Bayern's reserve team]] making 17 appearances during the [[2019–20 3. Liga|2019–20 season]].<ref name="2019–20 season">{{Cite magazine|title=Stiller Angelo |url=https://www.kicker.de/angelo-stiller/spieler/3-liga/2019-20/bayern-muenchen-ii |magazine=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |publisher=Olympia-Vertlag GmbH|access-date=15 December 2020 |language=de}}</ref> In October 2020, he made his debut for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in a 3–0 victory against [[1. FC Düren]] in the [[2020–21 DFB-Pokal]], replacing [[Niklas Süle]] in the second half.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/duren-bayern-munich-dfb-cup-live-line-ups-stats-lewandowski-sane-davies-13218 |title=Thomas Müller and Eric Maxim Choupo-Moting send Bayern Munich into DFB Cup second round with victory against Düren |website=Bundesliga |date=16 October 2020|access-date=9 July 2025}}</ref> On 1 December 2020, Stiller made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 1–1 away draw against [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://de.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029447--atletico-vs-bayern/ |title=Atlético 1–1 Bayern |website=UEFA |date=1 December 2020|language=de}}</ref>

=== TSG Hoffenheim ===
On 18 January 2021, Stiller joined [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] for the [[2021–22 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.kicker.de/wechsel-erst-im-sommer-bayern-talent-stiller-nach-hoffenheim-794460/artikel |title=Wechsel erst im Sommer: Bayern-Talent Stiller folgt Hoeneß nach Hoffenheim |magazine=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] | date = 18 January 2021 |access-date=18 January 2021 | language = de}}</ref> Later that year, on 15 December, he scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal in a 2–2 away draw against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2021/12/spektakulaere-aufholjagd-sichert-punktgewinn-in-leverkusen |title=Spektakuläre Aufholjagd sichert Punktgewinn in Leverkusen |publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim |language=de |date=15 December 2021 }}</ref>

=== VfB Stuttgart ===
On 25 August 2023, Stiller moved to [[VfB Stuttgart]] and signed a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/vfb-stuttgart-verpflichtet-angelo-stiller-/|title=VfB sign Angelo Stiller|website=[[VfB Stuttgart]]|date=25 August 2023|access-date=9 July 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club and provided an assist in a 3–3 draw against [[1. FC Heidenheim|Heidenheim]] on 31 March 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/stuttgart-vs-heidenheim/spielbericht/488571 |title=Wahnsinn in Stuttgart! Undav kontert Kleindienst-Show|website=[[Sky Sport (Germany)|Sky Sport Germany]]|publisher=Sky Group|language=de |date=1 April 2024 }}</ref> Later that year, on 11 December, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 5–1 victory over [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/stuttgart-young-boys-live-champions-league-blog-preview-report-undav-nubel-demirovic-29965 |title=Five-star VfB Stuttgart come from behind to keep alive hopes of UEFA Champions League progression |website=Bundesliga |date=12 December 2024 }}</ref> In January 2025, Stiller extended his contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2425/angelo-stiller-2028/ |title=Angelo Stiller verlängert vorzeitig beim VfB |website=VfB Stuttgart |language=de |date=28 January 2025 }}</ref>

== International career ==
Stiller was a youth international footballer for Germany;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/datencenter/personen/angelo-stiller/spieler|title=Angelo Stiller Personenprofil|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de}}</ref> he was also eligible to represent [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] internationally due to his maternal [[Croats in Germany|Croatian]] heritage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/omiljeni-vatreni-za-vl-da-su-se-nasi-malo-potrudili-imali-bi-igraca-iz-reala-majka-mu-je-hrvatica-1866336|title=Omiljeni vatreni za VL: Da su se naši malo potrudili imali bi igrača iz Reala, majka mu je Hrvatica|date=2025-06-03|access-date=2025-08-05|website=[[Večernji list]]|last=Janković|first=Željko|language=hr}}</ref> In August 2024, he was called up for the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]] ahead of the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|2024–25 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/nach-heim-em-nagelsmann-beruft-einen-neuen-und-zwei-rueckkehrer-263942/|title=Nach Heim-EM: Nagelsmann beruft einen Neuen und zwei Rückkehrer|date=29 August 2024|publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date=29 August 2024|language=de }}</ref> Stiller debuted for the senior team 7 September 2024 against Hungary at the [[Merkur Spiel-Arena]], replacing [[Robert Andrich]] in the 82nd minute of Germany's 5–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Kai|last=Winderl|title=Der neue Kroos? So lief das DFB-Debüt von Angelo Stiller|url=https://www.swp.de/unterhaltung/tv/vfb-stuttgart-der-neue-kroos-so-lief-das-dfb-debuet-von-angelo-stiller-77508437.html|newspaper=[[Südwest Presse]]|date=9 September 2024|access-date=9 July 2025|language=de}}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he was called-up by [[Julian Nagelsmann]] for the [[FIFA World Cup]], marking his [[2026 FIFA World Cup|first international tournament]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Zeitung |first=Stuttgarter |title=Der deutsche Kader steht: Welche Rolle spielen die vier VfB-Profis bei der WM? |url=https://www.stuttgarter-zeitung.de/inhalt.der-deutsche-kader-steht-welche-rolle-spielen-die-vier-vfb-profis-bei-der-wm.902b6c77-4395-4abc-9ce4-ca6c741160dc.html |access-date=2026-05-22 |website=stuttgarter-zeitung.de |language=de}}</ref>

